ced a note that had been left under his door.  Soulshiver, shivered as he realized that deep sleep had its price.  He cautiously went and picked up the note.  He quickly recognized Fergussens’s hand, and shook his head anew as he realized that he would have gotten help, whether or not he brought up Centuri’s plight a night ago or not.  More was at foot here than just Centuri’s capture and Tyvlain’s bid for power.  He tried to see the tangled skeins of the web that was being woven, but was aware that until he had Centuri safe and free from the clutches of his brother, life wasn’t going to get any clearer.  He sighed audibly and with deftness donned his armor.  Soulshiver paused a moment before opening his door.  As a Knight of Innoruuk, Soulshiver had always saluted his God for the strength and power that he provided him.  The litany taught to him as a youth, almost came unbidden to his lips as it had been a habit for nigh, 987 years.  He bit his lips as he quivered with rage, “Innoruuk, Dark Bastard.  Feel my Hate. Feel my Rage. The Night shall come where thou shalt die by my hands.  May that Night draw near. May I live to see thy blood.  This is my Prayer.”<br>
<br>
The forest of Netkulos provided comfort and solace for Soulshiver.  He spent his earliest years accomplishing tasks for his Masters in the gloom and murk the forest always provided.  The spiderling and skeleton infested place held many a nightmare for the young Shadow Knight and truly taught him the skills necessary to survive the many dangers of Norrath.  He looked over his shoulder to where five full, six member groups waited anxiously.  Kamal had just been gifted with the gift of the Spirit of the Wolf and was comically running around in circles, faster and faster, as he shouted, “Luk whad I kan du, Luk wad I kan du.”  His antics came to a sudden stop as slammed with significant force into a tree trunk that was twice his size.  He picked himself off the ground with a smile and said with a grin, “Me wishin’ dat tree wuz a Troooll.”  Soulshiver smiled at the young troll warrior and said, “Kamal, it is time.  Grab Kkallel and commence the Raid.” Incantations were whispered as the main of Blood Circle disappeared from view.  From his vantage point he watched with much amusement as Kamal and Kkallel gathered every insect, skeleton, and bear in a 3 mile radius.  Kamal was shouting, “Spiders!! Spiders!! Evewewhere!!!”  After amassing a literal horde of the creatures the troll and the ogre ran screaming and flailing wildly toward Neriak’s Main entrance.  The guards looked up from their watch with a look of horror as the wave of troll, ogre, and creature engulfed them in a rising tide.  As the picked themselves off the trampled ground and hurried after the tsunami of creatures, they had no chance noticing the 30 invisible companions entering Neriak. <br>
The watch and alarm was sounded as guards poured from every corner of Neriak.  Kamal and Kkallel continued the shouting and screaming until finally, a Wizard tired of the noise disturbing his meditation, rooted Kamal and Kkallel in place.  Thinking he had finally quieted his noisy disturbances, he re-opened his spell book to the page he had been studying.  He had just completed his first Rune when the troll and ogre shrieked in terrible fear as over 300 spiderling swarmed over them completely obscuring them from sight.  The Wizard quickly gated to a quiet and considerably safe location.  After about a minute of the spiderling attack, Kamal and Kkallel could bear no more, the fell to the floor crushing dozens of spiderling, laughing until tears came, saying to one another, “My dat be a nice spider dreess you do be weeern’.”  Guards went about the foreign quarter attempting to contain the creeping menace and keep them from entering Neriak’s Commons.  Shouts and screams echoed throughout the city as the alarm disturbed many a sleep.  The denizens of Neriak couldn’t remember the last time that such a public disturbance had been created.  The rescue of Centuri had commenced, the plan was in motion and all the world will see that nothing is stronger than Brotherhood, nothing….<br>
