<br>
Centuri shivered almost uncontrollably as the weight of her time in this place pressed down upon her.  She stood once more before the door of Tyvlain Dy'Truin's rooms, rooms she suspected once belonged to Soulshiver.  Her two Orc guards were trying to stand as far away from her as they could in the narrow corridor, while still appearing to have her under their complete control.  She smiled grimly. They weren't very successful at it.  She had built up a certain reputation for violence amongst Tyvlain's guards.  There were many of them that would most likely never bear offspring because of her.  Centuri couldn't help but think that was a good thing.   She looked up at the crest on the solid door in front of her.  Violence would not save her from this tormenter.  Self-loathing at her own cowardice engulfed her once more as she recalled how she had surrendered to him a few days before.  On her knees, on the stone floor of the prison, in front of a cell full of children, she had called him &quot;Master&quot;.  Only because she could not bear to watch the deaths of those innocent children.  Children that he would most likely kill anyhow.  <br>
<br>
The drugs the Dark Masters had given her still clouded her mind and made it difficult to think.  If she only had a sword, she would kill that manipulating bastard, Tyvlain.  But her sword was gone.  Idly she wondered where it was.  Did Tyvlain have it hanging over his mantle, always within sight but just out of her reach?  It would be like him to torture her that way.  Or had he just tossed it in the smelter and destroyed it completely?  Either way, at least he would not be able to use the sword himself.  Goddess-blessed, only the Koada'dal Paladin of Tunare who's name was etched in the hilt with magical runes could wield the Falchion.  A sword that would never be sold or traded, the blade would be buried with the paladin who wielded it.   Centuri's hand clenched on the empty air at her side.  Tyvlain had stripped away her defenses as he had stripped away her sword. <br>
