 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ucenturi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Centuri</A> at: 7/25/01 6:09:53 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#353535><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/usgtofarmstheofrid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SgtofArmsTheofrid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/24/01 10:12:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/fbloodcirclefrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yin and Yang</span><hr size=1> Returning to the dark streets of Neriak, Theofrid, blended with the busy activity.  He made his way from the Commons and the sewer entrance deep inside the &quot;underground&quot;, a dark decrepit place filled with all manners of businesses.  Now he crossed the main street of Neriak's 3rd Gate.  He entered the &quot;Cuisine Excelsior&quot;, a tavern known for it's sale of all liquors of Norrath.  Dressed as a Dark Elf Officer and with the aid of his mask, he ordered a private table in a corner that put both the main entrance and the kitchen door, the only means of entering the tavern, in plain sight.  He ordered an Erudite Brandy and gave the few onlookers a scowl of, &quot;I wish to drink alone&quot;, and let his mind go deep into his own thoughts.<br>
  The last message he had received from his good friend Fergussen had mentioned the Blood Circle's resolve in a rescue attempt and that they would act soon.  He had quickly made his plans that night in the Nektulos Forest, for he knew he had to assist this &quot;raid&quot; to free the Elven Paladin Centuri, not just out of friendship to his ranger friend, nor for the honor of fighting beside the brave members of the BC.  Not even out of his own sense of what is right and good in the Paladin of Tunare.  No, he was here for revenge.  A deeper frown crossed his face.  It is the chance to take more from those who had taken everything from him in his early life.  His family, his home, his childhood, yes, it was these Dark Elves themselves that had shaped their own fate this night.  He would be one of those who would bring down one of the most powerful houses in Neriak and it was them that had made him who he was today.  <br>
Theofrid drank from his brandy to wash the taste of something from his mouth.  &quot;Odd,&quot; he thought to himself, &quot;Is this guilt I taste?&quot;  He took another drought from the smooth liquid and turned his thoughts to his preparations.  <br>
After he had taken down the Dark Elf Necromancer, Theofrid had stripped him of many papers.  He had found in them, for his own ability to understand the dark elf tongue was well established, a letter from House Dy'truin, asking that House J'Narus be aware that they had &quot;a sacrifice&quot; that would elevate them to the number one House and their allies would reap the rewards also.  Theofrid smiled to himself, &quot;House Dy'truin was making a power play within Neriak, and it's current ruler, Tyvlain was thinking that this was his time.  Ahh, but not if I can help in it's ruin.&quot;  Theofrid also knew from Bithnira, the Inky whore in the deeper underground of Neriak, just when and where they planned the execution of the Elven paladin.  So he had acted quickly, traveling thru the dark forest to one of the many hidden entrances to the tunnels leading into the city.  He had silently dropped down behind the Dark Elf guard posted at the entrance and with a well placed poisoned dagger, passed back into the city.  He had removed his Dragoon Lieutenants' uniform earlier and had placed that with others items to aid his ranger friend in entering the city less noticeably down in the tunnels.  He had then had gone into the commons area, to the Forge House, a tavern of favor to the Dragoons of the city.  There he patiently waited, singling out a specific officer, just a little drunker than most, and waited for him to make his way to leave.  Shortly, in a ally wrapped in shadows, Theofrid emerged dressed like a dragoon Captain of the House Dy'Truin.  Then he turned up the street in the direction of Neriak's 3rd Gate.<br>
So now he drank again from his brandy.  Theofrid glanced at the candle on his table and realized how much time had passed.  &quot;Hmmm, he should be here any time now, if all went well.&quot;, he thought to himself.  Theofrid tossed down the last of his drink as the door opened and a dragoon officer entered.  He raised his head in acknowledgement when the eyes of the newcomer fell upon him.  Fergussen crossed the room and slowly took a seat next to Theofrid.  &quot;I am glad to see the new uniform fits you so well.&quot;, Theofrid said in the Dark tongue, just a hint of a smile in his face.  &quot;Time for one short drink to this eve and our success.&quot;  Theofrid raised his hand ordering two more of the Erudite Liquor.  &quot;We must be about our business, for the night draws late.&quot;  <br>
  The two dragoons rose from the table, crossed the tavern to the door and stepped into the thick oily air of the streets.  No words were spoken as the two made their way towards the House of Dy'Truin.<br>
